00:15:34.150 --> 00:15:34.750
&gt;&gt; Claire Wang: Dear
Katherine Paterson:

00:15:36.150 --> 00:15:37.550
What brings two completely
different people together

00:15:38.150 --> 00:15:38.750
and creates a lasting
bond between them.

00:15:40.150 --> 00:15:41.150
In what ways does it
change our lives forever?

00:15:42.150 --> 00:15:42.870
To me a friendship seems
useless and superficial.

00:15:44.630 --> 00:15:49.296
I believe that something or someone
will always break it or destroy it,

00:15:49.800 --> 00:15:51.800
erase it with no trace at all.

00:15:52.710 --> 00:15:52.836
When my family moved back to
Beijing, I lost all my best friends.

00:15:56.850 --> 00:15:57.450
Year's worth of friendship was
broken in a matter of minutes.

00:16:00.250 --> 00:16:03.983
I became bitter and cautious
to any potential companions.

00:16:04.270 --> 00:16:04.323
In a Chinese public school
I was known as the tall,

00:16:07.550 --> 00:16:07.860
think Chinese-American girl
who had no feelings at all.

00:16:10.840 --> 00:16:14.106
However I was indifferent
to the gossip around me.

00:16:14.600 --> 00:16:17.400
The hurtful gossip
further proved my point.

00:16:17.970 --> 00:16:18.310
Thankfully my parents transferred
me to a bilingual private school.

00:16:22.030 --> 00:16:22.560
Slowly but surely I became attached
to some of the people there.

00:16:25.700 --> 00:16:28.766
In that group of people
was a girl named Vicki.

00:16:30.140 --> 00:16:30.503
Her attitude and characteristics
were similar

00:16:32.710 --> 00:16:35.976
to your character Leslie
Burke, bright and lively,

00:16:37.500 --> 00:16:39.433
bold and somewhat rebellious.

00:16:39.980 --> 00:16:40.306
We helped with each
other's struggles.

00:16:42.120 --> 00:16:44.586
She was a leader and
I was a follower.

00:16:44.680 --> 00:16:45.250
Regardless of our completely
different personalities Vicki

00:16:47.910 --> 00:16:49.843
and I were soon best friends.

00:16:50.370 --> 00:16:53.370
Although my parents
started to home-school me,

00:16:54.100 --> 00:16:56.500
things remained the same between us.

00:16:56.500 --> 00:16:58.966
I thought I will always
see her again.

00:16:59.500 --> 00:17:00.500


00:17:00.530 --> 00:17:00.686
One cloudy day, someone
told me the shocking news.

00:17:03.640 --> 00:17:04.640
"Vicki's dead."

00:17:05.640 --> 00:17:08.506
I felt stunned and
helpless that entire day.

00:17:08.720 --> 00:17:11.120
A car accident took her bright life.

00:17:11.640 --> 00:17:12.096
Again, a perfect friendship was
destroyed in a matter of minutes.

00:17:15.450 --> 00:17:16.983
Again, I became bitter.

00:17:17.450 --> 00:17:18.263
Never again should I
ever rely on friendship.

00:17:19.570 --> 00:17:20.130
Never again should I
ever have a close friend.

00:17:22.010 --> 00:17:25.610
I repeated these promises to
myself almost every night.

00:17:26.720 --> 00:17:30.053
As books are one of my
escapes from the real world,

00:17:30.550 --> 00:17:34.883
I picked up the book Bridge to
Terabithia from my dusty bookshelf.

00:17:35.070 --> 00:17:35.746
Although I read Bridge
to Terabithia before,

00:17:37.260 --> 00:17:39.660
I felt something different
this time.

00:17:39.940 --> 00:17:40.376
I understood Jess Aaron's feelings
before Leslie came into his life.

00:17:43.970 --> 00:17:47.303
I smiled at the adventures
that Jess and Leslie had

00:17:48.650 --> 00:17:49.050
in their magical world
of Terabithia.

00:17:50.650 --> 00:17:51.453
I thought that their perfect
friendship would go on forever.

00:17:53.780 --> 00:17:54.086
I was shocked when Brenda
told Jess that Leslie is dead.

00:17:57.140 --> 00:18:01.140
That part is like a clear
reflection of my present situation.

00:18:01.780 --> 00:18:05.780
However, I was curious to see
how Jess reacted to this event.

00:18:07.380 --> 00:18:07.933
When I finished your book, I
knew immediately what to do.

00:18:10.560 --> 00:18:10.813
Just like Jess who passed down the
lessons that Leslie taught him,

00:18:14.640 --> 00:18:16.373
I will try to do the same.

00:18:16.640 --> 00:18:17.573
I will remember how Vicki impacted
others through her cheerful,

00:18:19.840 --> 00:18:20.306
creative spirit and
strong leadership.

00:18:21.840 --> 00:18:25.573
Instead of being timid and
shy, I will try to help others

00:18:26.500 --> 00:18:30.766
with my leadership and smile to
pass down the gift Vicki left me.

00:18:30.950 --> 00:18:35.083
I used to think that death marked
an ending, however now I know

00:18:35.880 --> 00:18:39.546
that it also marks a new
beginning for a new friendship.

00:18:39.560 --> 00:18:40.493
Thank you so much for teaching
me this valuable lesson

00:18:42.160 --> 00:18:43.360
through your book.

00:18:44.160 --> 00:18:45.393
Thank you for making me understand
how God intended friendship to be.

00:18:47.460 --> 00:18:48.993
Sincerely, Claire Wang.

