than it takes you to go
to your school library

00:30:56.130 --> 00:31:00.063
or your public library or the
bookstore and pick out a book.

00:31:01.290 --> 00:31:05.023
And it's just a marvelous
testament to the power of books

00:31:05.720 --> 00:31:09.386
to hear what those individual
books meant in your lives.

00:31:10.170 --> 00:31:10.833
And I think all of us
who love books have had

00:31:12.440 --> 00:31:14.373
that same kind of experience.

00:31:14.930 --> 00:31:19.530
Now it's true that you don't always
have to go to the library anymore.

00:31:20.170 --> 00:31:20.276
You can download books
to your Kindle.

00:31:22.530 --> 00:31:25.663
You can download books
from your public library.

00:31:27.870 --> 00:31:31.736
But you know you can't have an
author sign the Kindle book.

00:31:34.110 --> 00:31:34.690
[Laughter] And there's
something magical

00:31:36.130 --> 00:31:38.730
in having the author
sign that book too.

00:31:39.280 --> 00:31:43.746
I think we all want to give the
authors a special round of applause.

00:31:44.250 --> 00:31:45.250


00:31:51.510 --> 00:31:51.933
[Applause] So this is
the 10th anniversary

00:31:53.820 --> 00:31:53.876
of the National Book Festival
and we chose the theme:

00:31:57.230 --> 00:31:59.163
A Decade of Words and Wonder.

00:32:00.250 --> 00:32:03.183
And it is the words that
bring us the wonder.

00:32:05.100 --> 00:32:07.900
Good writers pave the
way for avid readers.

00:32:08.480 --> 00:32:11.013
Good readers often
become good writers.

00:32:12.100 --> 00:32:14.900
Books are the links of
a chain of knowledge

00:32:15.860 --> 00:32:17.860
and enjoyment that never ends.

00:32:19.500 --> 00:32:23.500
So all of you in this room please
keep reading, keep writing.

00:32:27.070 --> 00:32:31.336
Thank you for joining us today
and let's go on to the next decade

00:32:32.430 --> 00:32:34.430
of the National Book Festival.

00:32:34.430 --> 00:32:37.096
We'll see you again
right here next year.

00:32:38.030 --> 00:32:39.896
